  <section id="study-tips" class="container ace-section">
    <h2>Study Tips for A-Level Law</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Understand key cases:</strong> Don’t just memorize facts — focus on the legal principles and reasoning behind each case.</li>
      <li><strong>Practice IRAC method:</strong> Issue, Rule, Application, Conclusion — structure your essays clearly.</li>
      <li><strong>Use past papers:</strong> Familiarize yourself with exam style questions and time yourself while answering.</li>
      <li><strong>Create flashcards:</strong> Use them for definitions, case facts, and legal principles for active recall.</li>
      <li><strong>Form study groups:</strong> Explaining topics to peers deepens understanding.</li>
      <li><strong>Regular revision:</strong> Break study into manageable chunks and revisit topics regularly.</li>
      <li><strong>Stay updated:</strong> Follow recent legal developments and news related to your syllabus.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="ace-law" class="container ace-section">
    <h2>Ace Law Section: In-Depth Advice</h2>
    <p>Mastering A-Level Law is about strategy and consistency. Here’s a comprehensive approach:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Build Strong Foundations:</strong> Start with understanding the basic legal concepts and vocabulary. Don’t skip the theory behind the law.</li>
      <li><strong>Focus on Cases:</strong> Study each landmark case in detail. Know the facts, legal issues, judgments, and significance. Use official links to read the full judgments when possible.</li>
      <li><strong>Essay Writing:</strong> Perfect the IRAC structure for all essay questions. Always clearly state the issue, apply the relevant law, analyze with examples, and conclude decisively.</li>
      <li><strong>Past Papers:</strong> Complete at least one past paper every week in exam conditions. Review your answers critically or get feedback from teachers or peers.</li>
      <li><strong>Mind Maps & Summaries:</strong> Create visual aids to connect concepts and cases; they help with quick revision.</li>
      <li><strong>Exam Technique:</strong> Manage your time carefully during exams. Allocate marks proportionally and leave time to review your answers.</li>
      <li><strong>Ask for Help:</strong> Use forums, study groups, or AI tools like the chatbox here to clarify doubts quickly.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Helpful links for further study:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.aqa.org.uk/find-past-papers-and-mark-schemes" target="_blank" class="btn">AQA Past Papers</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.ocr.org.uk/qualifications/as-and-a-level/law-h015-h415/" target="_blank" class="btn">OCR Law Resources</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.jcq.org.uk/exams-office/past-papers/" target="_blank" class="btn">JCQ Past Papers</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

